{"questionId":"32404101","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In this question, all distances are in kilometres and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is in hours.<br>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> be a displacement of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math> due east, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> be a displacement of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math> due north, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> be a vertical displacement of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Highway 85 in Saudi Arabia is a long, straight, flat road.</p>\n<p>Relative to the centre of the town Arar, point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>, the position vector of a car, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>, travelling along this road is given by:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>OC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>10</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>50</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>33</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the speed of the car.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that speed is the magnitude of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>50</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>33</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mn>50</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>33</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math> &nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>50</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>33</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>59</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>km</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>59</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9082</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32404101","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the speed of the car.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Vector definitions","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.11—Vector equation of a line in 2d and 3d","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector applications to kinematics","Topic 3—Geometry